Pigsty Python Faker backport
============================

This recipe is based on Ubuntu Noble's official faker 22.0.0-1 source package:

  https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/faker/22.0.0-1

It uses the official faker_22.0.0.orig.tar.gz unchanged.  The recipe keeps the
official pybuild packaging model but builds only python3-fake-factory, which is
the runtime package required by postgresql-*-faker.  The separate faker CLI
package, its generated manual page, and upstream's large optional pytest stack
are intentionally omitted from this runtime-only backport.

The Makefile permits builds only on bookworm and jammy and appends the suite to
the Debian version.  Trixie, Noble, and Resolute must continue to use their
distribution packages.
